February 2022 I made a decision within my heart, in a hotel room, to drop my old life and follow Jesus. 

July 1 2023 - Today, I got baptized 🥹 

Thank you Jesus for saving me, life was so so dark without you ❤️

To anyone who may be feeling like life is meaningless, maybe you’re at your wits end, confused about your purpose, or maybe struggling with depression & anxiety — try Jesus 🙏🏾 

I always knew about God  growing up Christian, but at no point was I ever willing to live how the Bible calls us to live and I definitely had some doubts about how real Jesus was. And I didn’t care to look into it 🤷🏾‍♀️ (just being honest) 

I did not want to let go of the life I was living, and accept the life Jesus had for me. Until I reached a point where nothing ever seemed like enough. I had it all yet I felt like I was still searching for something but didn’t know what I was searching for. I was tired, broken, and couldn’t keep on. I knew I couldn’t keep living how I was living or it wouldn’t end well for me no matter how great I seemed on the outside.

It was only when I decided to surrender the life I believe I had built and said “Jesus, you can have me” that I finally experienced the Jesus I heard so much about for myself.

Jesus is so so real guys like fr (I wouldn’t blow my whole life up like this if He wasn’t 😂) and He loves you and I soooooo much it makes no sense! You that is reading this, He knows exactly who you are & He wants you to get to know His true nature; not to have a religious relationship but a personal relationship.

If that is something you’re interested in, make a decision in your heart to surrender your life, your desires, your habits, your everything to follow Jesus. In due time, Jesus will show you just how real and true He is and His unconditional love for you. 

I’ve found true peace & joy, no amount of money can ever buy that. 

Happy July friends 💕

@lesley.osei @domosei @kingdomfulltabernacle

The word for August is “be careful” 😭

How do you guys feel about family commenting on weight gain (or loss)? You all know I’m very big on body positivity and keeping comments to yourself regarding someone else’s weight. However, I come from a Nigerian background where no one cares lmao And it seems no matter the culture, this is a shared experience. So what do we do? Change the perspective? Does it depend who it’s coming from? How the message is delivered? 
For me, I don’t mind a little accountability from a trusted source and delivered with love, I think it’s necessary to an extent. But if I don’t know you like that, go pray about it because I don’t want to hear it from you!!! 

Let’s talk about it ⬇️

Hair: @chisluxebraidinghair 

#bodyimage #bodypositivity #weightgain #weightloss #africanparents

What is something you’re currently saving for? Is it a trip? A new purse? Makeup? But what if you’re not even thinking about saving for anything and just spend and buy the things that you want at the exact moment you get paid?

Smart spending habits are important and saving your money is even more important, not only for today but for your future. If you’re thinking about starting your savings journey, it may seem like it now, but trust me - it doesn’t have to be overwhelming. No matter what your income is, having savings and healthy spending habits are important for every aspect of your life: present + future.

I know for a fact that once I started making money, I didn’t even think about saving. When I saw those numbers roll in, I started spending like crazy and next thing I knew, my paycheck was gone and I had to wait for the next one to roll in to keep moving forward. The best thing I did for myself was learning smart money habits. I knew living paycheck to paycheck wasn’t going to get me anywhere so I sat down and re-evaluated how I wanted my finances to look.

One way to get started on your savings journey is with the Fidelity Bloom® app which is a free financial app that helps you save more and build long-lasting habits. It includes two brokerage accounts—one for saving, one for spending. You can earn cash rewards with a linked debit card and you’ll receive $100 when you deposit $50 or more. Offer ends 12/11/23.
